question:
Reformatted Question: In the census of 2010, there were 66,135 people, 26,265 (2000 data) households, and 14,051 (2000 data) families residing in the city. The population density was 6,096.7 people per square mile (2,199.9/km²). There were 30,272 (2000 data) housing units at an average density of 2,790.6 per square mile (1,077.2/km²). The racial makeup of the city was 59.38% (52.31% Non-Hispanic) (7.07 White-Hispanic) White (U.S. Census), 24.19% African American (U.S. Census), 14.47% Hispanic (U.S. Census) or Latin (U.S. Census)) of any race, 8.24% from Race (United States Census), 5.74% from two or more races, 2.62% Asian (U.S. Census), 0.69%  Native American (U.S.Census), and 0.14% Pacific Islander (U.S. Census). There is a growing Guyana population in the area. The top ancestries self-identified by people on the census are <fact1>Italian (13.6%)</fact1>, <fact2>Guyanese (12.3%)</fact2>, <fact3>Irish (12.1%)</fact3>, Puerto Rican (10.1%), German (8.7%), English (6.0%), <fact4>Polish (5.4%)</fact4>, French (4.4%). These reflect historic and early 20th-century immigration, as well as that since the late 20th century. How many percent more people were in the the second largest group compared to the second smallest?

Answer: The question asks the difference between the second largest and second smallest ancestry groups.  The passage lists ancestries in descending order.
<fact2>The second largest group is Guyanese at 12.3%</fact2>.
<fact4>The second smallest group listed is Polish at 5.4%</fact4>.

12.3% - 5.4% = 6.9%

So the answer is {6.9}.

Reformatted Question: After a franchise record setting performance the Saints went to face another winless team, the St. Louis Rams. This time, however, the Rams pulled off one of the best upsets in the NFL season. A defense kept the Saints scoreless for the first half. The second the Rams sealed the deal with an interception return for 27 yards. With this <fact1>the Saints fell to 5-3</fact1>. However this would be the last time the Saints would lose in the regular season. How many losses did the Saints have coming into this game?

Answer: The passage states that <fact1>the Saints record fell to 5 wins and 3 losses</fact1> after this game. Thus, they had 3 losses coming into this game. So the answer is {3}.

Reformatted Question: In the Morean War, the Republic of Venice <fact1>besieged Sinj</fact1> in October 1684 and then again March and April 1685, but both times without success. In the 1685 attempt, the Venetian armies were aided by the local militia of the Republic of Poljica, who thereby rebelled against their nominal Ottoman suzerainty that had existed since 1513. In an effort to retaliate to Poljica, in June 1685, the Ottomans attacked Zadvarje, and in July 1686 Dolac and Srijane, but were pushed back, and suffered major casualties. With the help of the local population of Poljica as well as the Morlachs, the <fact2>fortress of Sinj finally fell</fact2> to the Venetian army on 30 September 1686. On 1 September 1687 the <fact3>siege of Herceg Novi started</fact3>, and ended with a Venetian victory on 30 September. <fact4>Knin was taken</fact4> after a twelve-day siege on 11 September 1688. The capture of the Knin Fortress marked the end of the successful Venetian campaign to expand their territory in inland Dalmatia, and it also determined much of the final border between Dalmatia and Bosnia and Herzegovina that stands today. The Ottomans would besiege Sinj again in the Second Morean War, but would be repelled. On 26 November 1690, <fact5>Venice took Vrgorac</fact5>, which opened the route towards Imotski and Mostar. In 1694 they <fact6>managed to take areas north of the Republic of Ragusa</fact6>, namely Čitluk, Gabela, Zažablje, Trebinje, Popovo, Klobuk and Metković. In the final peace treaty, Venice did relinquish the areas of Popovo polje as well as Klek and Sutorina, to maintain the pre-existing demarcation near Ragusa. How many cities did Venice try to take?


Answer: Venice attempted to take the following cities: <fact1>Sinj</fact1> (successfully on the third attempt), <fact3>Herceg Novi</fact3>, <fact4>Knin</fact4>, and <fact5>Vrgorac</fact5>.  <fact6>They also took multiple areas north of Ragusa</fact6>, though the question asks about cities and the passage lists several specific locations, suggesting these are smaller settlements rather than cities.  Therefore, Venice tried to take 4 cities. So the answer is {4}.

**Reformatted Question:** Led by former Giant Kurt Warner, the defending NFC champions took the field at Giants Stadium against a Giants team still reeling from their bad loss in New Orleans. The Giants scored first, sending Jacobs in for a 4-yard touchdown run following a <fact1>Terrell Thomas interception</fact1>. Later, Arizona running back Beanie Wells scored his first career touchdown on a 13-yard rush. Manning responded by throwing a 62-yard touchdown to Nicks for his longest reception of the year. In the second half, the Cardinals' Tim Hightower and Jason Wright scored touchdowns. But it was turnovers that decided this game; <fact2>Manning's 3 interceptions</fact2> were as many as he had thrown all season. The Giants scored only 3 points in the second half, ending the game on an <fact3>interception to Antrel Rolle</fact3>. The Giants notable streak of 38 consecutive starts by the same offensive line unit was ended here, as offensive tackle Kareem McKenzie missed the game with a groin injury. McKenzie returned the following week. How many interceptions did Arizona catch?


**Answer:** The question asks how many interceptions *Arizona* caught. The passage states that there was <fact1>one interception by Terrell Thomas</fact1>, which resulted in a Giants touchdown.  It also mentions <fact2>three interceptions thrown by Manning</fact2> and that the game ended on an <fact3>interception by Antrel Rolle</fact3>. Since Manning was the Giants' quarterback, and Rolle plays for the Giants, the <fact2>three interceptions of Manning</fact2> and the <fact3>interception by Rolle</fact3> were all caught by Arizona. Therefore, Arizona caught 3 + 1 = 4 interceptions.  So the answer is {4}.

Reformatted Question: In 1997, Russia and Ukraine signed the Partition Treaty, establishing two independent national fleets and dividing armaments and bases between them. Ukraine also agreed to lease major parts of its facilities to the Russian Black Sea Fleet <fact1>until 2017</fact1>. However, the treaty appeared to be far from perfect: permanent tensions on the lease details control continued. The Fleet's main base is still situated in the Crimean port city of Sevastopol. In 2009 the Yushchenko Ukrainian government declared that the lease would not be extended and that the fleet would have to leave Sevastopol <fact1>by 2017</fact1>.  In <fact2>2010</fact2> the Russian leasehold was renegotiated with an extension <fact3>until 2042</fact3> and an option for an additional five years <fact4>until 2047</fact4>. How many years was the leasehold renegotiated for?

Answer: The passage says the lease was renegotiated in <fact2>2010</fact2> and extended <fact3>until 2042</fact3>, with an option for 5 more years <fact4>until 2047</fact4>.  2042 - 2010 = 32 years. Including the optional 5 years, the renegotiated lease was for 32 + 5 = 37 years. Since the question asks "How many years *was* the leasehold renegotiated for", this implies the initial agreement, not including the optional extension. Therefore the answer is {32}.

**Reformatted Question:** The number of entrants has increased greatly in recent years. In the FA Cup 2004-05 season, 660 clubs entered the competition, beating the long-standing record of 656 from the 1921-22 season. In 2005-06 FA Cup this increased to 674 entrants, in 2006-07 FA Cup to 687, in 2007-08 FA Cup to 731 clubs, and for the <fact1>2008-09 FA Cup</fact1> and 2009-10 FA Cup competitions it reached 762. The number has varied slightly but remained roughly stable since then, with <fact2>759 clubs participating in 2010-11 FA Cup</fact2>, a record <fact3>763 in 2011-12 FA Cup</fact3>, 758 for 2012-13 FA Cup, 737 for 2013-14 FA Cup and 736 for 2014-15 FA Cup. By comparison, the other major English domestic cup, the EFL Cup, involves only the 92 members of the Premier League and Football League. How many times after <fact1>2008-09 FA Cup</fact1> and before <fact3>the 2011-12 FA Cup</fact3> was there an entrance of over 760 clubs?


**Answer:** We are looking for the number of times the entrant count exceeded 760 between the <fact1>2008-09</fact1> and <fact3>2011-12</fact3> FA Cups.  The passage tells us there were <fact2>759 entrants in the 2010-11 FA Cup</fact2>.  Since 759 is not over 760, there were zero seasons with more than 760 entrants between 2008-09 and 2011-12.  Therefore, the answer is {0}.

**Reformatted Question:** Hoping to rebound from their divisional loss to the Jaguars, the Texans stayed at home for a Week 4 duel with the Oakland Raiders.  Houston delivered the opening shot of the first quarter with <fact1>kicker Kris Brown's 26-yard field goal</fact1>, followed by the Raiders tying the game with a <fact2>46-yard field goal from kicker Sebastian Janikowski</fact2>.  The Texans would take full command in the second quarter as <fact1>Brown nailed a 34-yard field goal</fact1>, followed by running back Steve Slaton getting a 32-yard touchdown run and catching an 18-yard touchdown pass from quarterback Matt Schaub.  Oakland would close out the half with <fact2>Janikowski's 33-yard field goal</fact2>.  In the third quarter, Houston would continue its domination with rookie linebacker Brian Cushing tackling Raiders running back Justin Fargas in his own endzone for a safety, immediately followed by wide receiver Jacoby Jones returning a kickoff 95 yards for a touchdown. How many more yards was Janikowski's longest field goal over Brown's longest one?


**Answer:**  According to the passage, <fact2>Janikowski's longest field goal was 46 yards</fact2> and <fact1>Brown's longest field goal was 34 yards</fact1>. <fact2>46</fact2> - <fact1>34</fact1> = 20. So the answer is {20}.

**Reformatted Question:** Hoping to rebound from their divisional loss to the Jaguars, the Texans stayed at home for a Week 4 duel with the Oakland Raiders.  Houston delivered the opening shot of the first quarter with <fact1>kicker Kris Brown's 26-yard field goal</fact1>, followed by the Raiders tying the game with a 46-yard field goal from kicker Sebastian Janikowski.  The Texans would take full command in the second quarter as <fact2>Brown nailed a 34-yard field goal</fact2>, followed by running back Steve Slaton getting a 32-yard touchdown run and catching an 18-yard touchdown pass from quarterback Matt Schaub.  Oakland would close out the half with Janikowski's 33-yard field goal.  In the third quarter, Houston would continue its domination with rookie linebacker Brian Cushing tackling Raiders running back Justin Fargas in his own endzone for a safety, immediately followed by wide receiver Jacoby Jones returning a kickoff 95 yards for a touchdown. How many yards longer was the second field goal than the first?


**Answer:** According to the passage, <fact1>Brown's first field goal was 26 yards</fact1> and <fact2>his second was 34 yards</fact2>.  <fact2>34</fact2> - <fact1>26</fact1> = 8. So the answer is {8}.

Reformatted Question: In January 1918, Romanian forces established control over Bessarabia as the Russian Army abandoned the province. Although a treaty was signed by the Romanian and Bolshevik Russian governments following <fact1>talks between 5 and 9 March 1918</fact1> on the withdrawal of Romanian forces from Bessarabia within two months, on 27 March 1918 Romania formally attached Bessarabia to its territory, based on a resolution passed by the local assembly of that territory on its unification with Romania. Romania officially made peace with the Central Powers by signing the Treaty of Bucharest on 7 May 1918. Under the treaty, Romania was obliged to end the war with the Central Powers and make small territorial concessions to Austria-Hungary, ceding control of some passes in the Carpathian Mountains, and to grant oil concessions to Germany. In exchange, the Central Powers recognised the sovereignty of Romania over Bessarabia. The treaty was renounced in October 1918 by the Alexandru Marghiloman government, and Romania nominally re-entered the war on 10 November 1918. The next day, the Treaty of Bucharest was nullified by the terms of the Armistice of Compiègne. Total Romanian deaths from 1914 to 1918, military and civilian, within contemporary borders, were estimated at 748,000. How many days did the talks between Russians and Romanians last?

Answer: The passage states that talks occurred <fact1>between 5 and 9 March 1918</fact1>.  That means the talks lasted 9 - 5 = 4 days.  However, since both the 5th and the 9th are included, we must add 1 to this result. Therefore, the talks lasted 4 + 1 = 5 days. So the answer is {5}.

Reformatted Question: Hoping to rebound from their season-opening loss to the Jaguars, the Broncos played on home ground for an interconference duel with the Seattle Seahawks. In the first quarter, the Broncos took the early lead, as quarterback Kyle Orton completed a 13-yard touchdown pass to wide receiver Eddie Royal, followed in the second quarter by a <fact1>1-yard touchdown run from running back Correll Buckhalter</fact1> and a 20-yard field goal by placekicker Matt Prater. The Seahawks got on the board in the third quarter, when quarterback Matt Hasselbeck completed an 11-yard touchdown pass to wide receiver Ben Obomanu, but the Broncos replied with a <fact2>1-yard touchdown run from running back Knowshon Moreno</fact2>. The Broncos increased their lead in the fourth quarter, when Orton threw a 21-yard touchdown pass to wide receiver Demaryius Thomas. The Seahawks replied, with Hasselbeck scrambling 20 yards for a touchdown, but the Broncos' lead was too much for Seattle to overcome. How many total yards of rushing touchdowns were scored?

Answer: According to the passage, Correll Buckhalter had a <fact1>1-yard touchdown run</fact1>, and Knowshon Moreno had a <fact2>1-yard touchdown run</fact2>.  <fact1>1</fact1> + <fact2>1</fact2> = 2. So the answer is {2}.

Reformatted Question: Of those aged 15 or over, 7,857,370 (51.6%) were economically active, 4,199,558 (27.6%) did Homemaking, <fact1>1,431,105 (9.4%) were students</fact1>, 914,934 (6.0%) were unable to work and 346,084 (2.3%) were pensioners. 521,938 (6.6%) of the economically active were unemployed. 604,540 Sri Lankans were living aboard for more than six months but were intending to return to Sri Lanka, mostly in the Arab states of the Persian Gulf (373,050 61.7%). How many in percent of those aged 15 and over weren't students?


Answer: According to the passage, <fact1>9.4% of those aged 15 and over were students</fact1>.  Therefore, the percentage of those who were not students is 100% - <fact1>9.4%</fact1> = 90.6%. So the answer is {90.6}.

**Reformatted Question:** In the county, the population was spread out with <fact1>26.20% under the age of 18</fact1>, <fact2>9.30% from 18 to 24</fact2>, <fact3>26.50% from 25 to 44</fact3>, <fact4>23.50% from 45 to 64</fact4>, and <fact5>14.60% who were 65 years of age or older</fact5>.  The median age was 37 years. For every 100 females there were 95.90 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 92.50 males. How many more people, in terms of percentage, were in the 2nd and 3rd largest age groups combined compared to the largest?

**Answer:**

1. **Identify the largest group:**  <fact1>The largest age group is under 18, representing 26.20% of the population.</fact1>

2. **Identify the 2nd and 3rd largest groups:** The next largest groups are <fact3>25 to 44 (26.50%)</fact3> and <fact4>45 to 64 (23.50%)</fact4>.

3. **Combine the 2nd and 3rd largest groups:** <fact3>26.50%</fact3> + <fact4>23.50%</fact4> = 50%

4. **Calculate the difference:** 50% - <fact1>26.20%</fact1> = 23.8%

So the answer is {23.8}.

**Reformatted Question:** Coming off their home win over the Vikings, the Saints flew to Candlestick Park for a Week 2 Monday Night duel with the San Francisco 49ers.  New Orleans would deliver the opening punch in the first quarter as 49ers center David Baas' high snap deep within San Francisco territory went out of the back of the endzone for a safety.  The Saints would add onto their lead as quarterback Drew Brees hooked up with running back Reggie Bush on a 6-yard touchdown pass.  The 49ers would answer in the second quarter as quarterback Alex Smith found running back Frank Gore on a 12-yard touchdown pass. San Francisco would take the lead with running back Anthony Dixon's 2-yard touchdown run, yet New Orleans would respond with Brees' 3-yard touchdown pass to tight end David Thomas.  <fact1>The Saints would add onto their lead in the fourth quarter as kicker Garrett Hartley made a 46-yard and a 19-yard field goal.</fact1>  The 49ers would strike back as Gore got a 7-yard touchdown run, followed by Smith's 2-point conversion pass to tight end Vernon Davis.  In the end, New Orleans got the last laugh as Hartley booted the game-ending 37-yard field goal. How many field goals did Garrett Hartley kick in the fourth quarter?


**Answer:** The passage states that <fact1>in the fourth quarter, Garrett Hartley kicked a 46-yard and a 19-yard field goal</fact1>. This means he kicked two field goals in the fourth quarter. So the answer is {2}.

Reformatted Question: Charles V returned to Spain on July 16, 1522.  Acts of repression and retaliation against former comuneros did occur, but only sporadically.  Embarrassingly large numbers of important people had supported the comuneros, or at least were suspiciously slow to declare allegiance to the king, and Charles thought it unwise to press the issue too much. Back in Valladolid, Charles declared a general pardon on November 1.  The pardon gave amnesty to everyone involved in the revolt with the exception of <fact1>293 comuneros</fact1>, a small figure given the huge number of rebels.  Both Pacheco and Bishop Acuña were among the <fact1>293</fact1> excluded from the pardon.  More pardons were issued later, after pressure from the Cortes; by 1527, the repression was completely at end.  Of the <fact1>293</fact1>, <fact2>23 were executed</fact2>, <fact3>20 died in prison</fact3>, <fact4>50 purchased amnesty</fact4>, and <fact5>100 were pardoned later</fact5>.  The fates of the rest are unknown. How many of the <fact1>293</fact1> prisoners were not pardoned, purchased amnesty or were executed?

Answer: The passage states that out of the <fact1>293 comuneros</fact1> excluded from the initial pardon, <fact2>23 were executed</fact2>, <fact3>20 died in prison</fact3>, <fact4>50 purchased amnesty</fact4>, and <fact5>100 were pardoned later</fact5>.  This accounts for <fact2>23</fact2> + <fact3>20</fact3> + <fact4>50</fact4> + <fact5>100</fact5> = 193 comuneros.  Since there were <fact1>293</fact1> total, the number whose fates are unknown is <fact1>293</fact1> - 193 = 100.  So the answer is {100}.

Reformatted Question: Another factor in the revolt of 1381 was the conduct of the war with France. In 1337 Edward III of England had pressed his claims to the French throne, beginning a long-running conflict that became known as the Hundred Years' War. Edward had initial successes, but his campaigns were not decisive. Charles V of France became more active in the conflict after 1369, taking advantage of his country's greater economic strength to commence cross-Channel raids on England. By the 1370s, England's armies on the continent were under huge military and financial pressure; <fact1>the garrisons in Calais and Brest alone, for example, were costing £36,000 a year to maintain</fact1>, while <fact2>military expeditions could consume £50,000 in only six months</fact2>. Edward died in 1377, leaving the throne to his grandson, Richard II, then only ten years old. How many £ was the cost for a year of the garrisons in Calais and Brest and what military expeditions could consume?


Answer: According to the passage, <fact1>the garrisons in Calais and Brest cost £36,000 a year</fact1>. <fact2>Military expeditions could consume £50,000 in six months</fact2>. This means that in a year, military expeditions could cost £50,000 * 2 = £100,000. So the yearly cost for the garrisons in Calais and Brest is £36,000, and yearly military expeditions could consume £100,000.

Reformatted Question: Coming off their divisional home win over the Rams, the 49ers flew to Texas Stadium for a Week 12 game with the throwback-clad Dallas Cowboys.  In the first quarter, the Niners struck first as kicker Joe Nedney got a 23-yard and a 22-yard field goal.  In the second quarter, the Cowboys took the lead as QB Tony Romo completed a 75-yard TD pass to former 49ers WR Terrell Owens.  Dallas continued its domination as LB Carlos Polk blocked punter Andy Lee's punt into the back of the endzone for a safety.  The Cowboys closed out its period of power as kicker <fact1>Nick Folk</fact1> got a <fact2>48-yard</fact2> and a <fact3>41-yard</fact3> field goal, along with Romo completing a 1-yard TD pass to TE Martellus Bennett. In the third quarter, Dallas increased its lead with Romo completing a 10-yard TD pass to WR Patrick Crayton.  San Francisco tried to rally as Nedney got a 35-yard field goal.  In the fourth quarter, the Cowboys answered with <fact1>Nick Folk</fact1> getting a <fact4>47-yard</fact4> field goal.  The 49ers tried to come back as QB Shaun Hill completed an 18-yard TD pass to WR Isaac Bruce, but Dallas replied with <fact1>Nick Folk</fact1> nailing a <fact5>42-yard</fact5> field goal.  The Niners tried to rally as Hill completed a 9-yard TD pass to RB DeShaun Foster, but that would be as close as San Francisco's comeback would get. How many field goals over 30 yards did Nick Folk make?

Answer: Nick Folk made three field goals over 30 yards: a <fact2>48-yard</fact2> field goal in the second quarter, a <fact4>47-yard</fact4> field goal in the fourth quarter, and a <fact5>42-yard</fact5> field goal also in the fourth quarter.  Therefore, the answer is {3}.

Reformatted Question: Other instances of napalms use include by France during the First Indochina War (1946-1954), the Algerian War of Independence (1954-1962), the Portuguese Colonial War (1961-1974), the Six-Day War by Israel (1967), in Nigeria (1969), India and Pakistan (1965 and 1971), Egypt (1973), by Morocco during the Western Sahara War (1975-1991), by Argentina (1982), by <fact1>Iran (1980-88)</fact1>, by <fact2>Iraq (1980-88)</fact2>, by Angola during the Angolan Civil War, and Yugoslav Wars (1991-1996). How many wars happened from 1980 to 1988?

Answer: The passage mentions two wars that occurred between 1980 and 1988: <fact1>the Iran-Iraq War (1980-1988)</fact1> and <fact2>the war involving Iraq during the same period (1980-1988)</fact2>.  Since the Iran-Iraq War involves both countries, these two mentions refer to the same war.  Therefore, there is only {1} war mentioned that occurred between 1980 and 1988.

Reformatted Question: With the end of the "crack epidemic" in the mid-1990s and with the initiation of aggressive policing under mayors David Dinkins and subsequently  Rudolph Giuliani, crime in Harlem plummeted. In <fact1>1981</fact1>, <fact2>6,500 robberies</fact2> were reported in Harlem; robberies dropped to 4,800 in 1990 during David Dinkins mayoralty. By <fact3>2000</fact3>, only 1,700 robberies were reported, and by 2010, only 1,100 were reported. There have been similar changes in all categories of crimes tracked by the New York City Police Department. In the 32nd Precinct, which services Central Harlem above 127th Street, for example, between 1990 and 2013, the murder rate dropped 89.4%, the rape rate dropped 67.5%, the robbery rate dropped 74.2%, burglary dropped 93.4%, and the total number of crime complaints dropped 77.6%. How many years since <fact1>1981</fact1> did the robberies drop?
Answer: According to the passage, the robberies dropped by <fact3>2000</fact3>. <fact3>2000</fact3> - <fact1>1981</fact1> = 19. So the answer is {19}.

Reformatted Question: As of the census of 2000, there were 19,234 people, 7,473 households, and 4,954 families residing in the village. The population density was 10,337.3 people per square mile (3,992.6/km²). There were 7,650 housing units at an average density of 4,111.5/sq mi (1,588.0/km²). The racial makeup of the village was <fact1>82.39% White (U.S. Census)</fact1>, <fact2>1.03% African American (U.S. Census)</fact2>, <fact3>0.29% Native American (U.S. Census)</fact3>, <fact4>4.52% Asian (U.S. Census)</fact4>, <fact5>0.04% Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)</fact5>, 3.93% from Race (United States Census), and 3.79% from two or more races. 13.03% of the population is Hispanic (U.S. Census) or Latino (U.S. Census) of any race. How many more people, in terms of percentage, were in the two biggest racial groups combined compared to the two smallest groups combined?

Answer: According to the passage, the two biggest racial groups are <fact1>White (82.39%)</fact1> and <fact4>Asian (4.52%)</fact4>, and the two smallest groups are <fact5>Pacific Islander (0.04%)</fact5> and <fact3>Native American (0.29%)</fact3>. The sum of the two biggest groups is <fact1>82.39%</fact1> + <fact4>4.52%</fact4> = 86.91%, and the sum of the two smallest groups is <fact5>0.04%</fact5> + <fact3>0.29%</fact3> = 0.33%. The difference between the two sums is 86.91% - 0.33% = 86.58%. So the answer is {86.58}.

Reformatted Question: Though there had been popular support for the war among the Russian public following the Japanese attack at Port Arthur in 1904, that popular support soon turned to discontent after suffering multiple defeats at the hands of the Japanese forces. For many Russians, the immediate shock of unexpected humiliation at the hands of Japan caused the conflict to be viewed as a metaphor for the shortcomings of the Romanov autocracy. Popular discontent in Russia after the war added more fuel to the already simmering <fact1>Russian Revolution of 1905</fact1>, an event Nicholas II had hoped to avoid entirely by taking intransigent negotiating stances prior to coming to the table. Twelve years later, that discontent boiled over into the <fact2>February Revolution of 1917</fact2>. In Poland, which Russia partitioned in the late 18th century, and where Russian rule already caused two major uprisings, the population was so restless that an army of 250,000-300,000—larger than the one facing the Japanese—had to be stationed to put down the unrest. Some political leaders of the Polish insurrection movement  sent emissaries to Japan to collaborate on sabotage and intelligence gathering within the Russian Empire and even plan a Japanese-aided uprising. In Russia, the defeat of 1905 led in the short term to a reform of the Russian military that allowed it to face Germany in World War I. However, the revolts at home following the war planted seeds that presaged the <fact3>Russian Revolution of 1917</fact3>. This was because Tsar Nicholas II issued the October Manifesto, which included only limited reforms such as the Duma and failed to address the societal problems of Russia at the time. How many revolutions did Russia suffer in the early 20th century?

Answer: According to the passage, there were <fact1>the Russian Revolution of 1905</fact1> and <fact2>the February Revolution of 1917</fact2>, which is also referred to as <fact3>the Russian Revolution of 1917</fact3>. However, <fact2>the February Revolution of 1917</fact2> and <fact3>the Russian Revolution of 1917</fact3> are the same event. Therefore, there were 2 revolutions in total. So the answer is {2}.

Reformatted Question: Hoping to increase their winning streak the Titans played on home ground for an Interconference duel with the Eagles. In the second quarter the Titans trailed with kicker <fact1>David Akers making a 25-yard field goal</fact1>. But they put themselves ahead with QB Kerry Collins completing a 26-yard TD pass to WR Kenny Britt. The Eagles replied with QB Kevin Kolb making a <fact2>5-yard TD pass to WR Riley Cooper</fact2>, followed by kicker <fact3>David Akers hitting a 46-yard field goal</fact3>. In the third quarter the Titans fell further behind with <fact4>Akers making a 46-yard field goal</fact4>. They soon replied with kicker Rob Bironas nailing a 41-yard field goal, but the Eagles continued to score in the 4th with <fact5>Akers getting a 28-yard field goal</fact5>. Eventually, they rallied to take a big lead with Collins completing an 80-yard TD pass to Britt, followed by Bironas hitting a 38-yard field goal. Then Collins found Britt for the third time in the game on a 16-yard TD pass, and then Bironas made a 33-yard field goal. The Titans continued to get their momentum going with CB Cortland Finnegan returning an interception 41 yards for a touchdown. How many points did the eagles get on the board with??
Answer: According to the passage, the Eagles scored with a <fact1>25-yard field goal (3 points)</fact1>, a <fact2>5-yard TD pass (7 points)</fact2>, a <fact3>46-yard field goal (3 points)</fact3>, a <fact4>46-yard field goal (3 points)</fact4>, and a <fact5>28-yard field goal (3 points)</fact5>. 3 + 7 + 3 + 3 + 3 = 19. So the answer is {19}.

Reformatted Question: Hoping to rebound from their loss to the Texans, the Bengals stayed at home for a <fact1>Week 7</fact1> inter conference duel with the Chicago Bears.  In the first quarter, Cincinnati got off to a fast start as quarterback Carson Palmer completed a 9-yard touchdown pass to wide receiver Chris Henry and an 8-yard touchdown pass to wide receiver Chad Ochocinco.  The Bengals would continue their dominating day in the second quarter as Palmer found tight end J.P. Foschi on a 3-yard touchdown pass and wide receiver Laveranues Coles on an 8-yard touchdown pass, followed by kicker Shayne Graham booting a 29-yard field goal. Reformatted Question: In 1905, 1,003 Korean immigrants, which included 802 men and 231 women and children, departed from the port of Chemulpo, Incheon aboard the ship Ilford to Salina Cruz, Oaxaca, Mexico. In the Veracruz port, another boat was taken to the port of Progreso with the final destination being the capital city of Mérida, Yucatan. Many of these Koreans were distributed throughout the Yucatán in 32 henequen haciendas. The town of Motul, Yucatan, located in the heart of the henequen zone, was a destination for many of the Korean immigrants. While Korean girls were much more subject to marriages arranged by Korean parents, males had greater freedom when it came to making a family. This rapid intermarriage by Koreans, coupled with geographic dispersal, prevented the establishment of close social networks among these migrants and therefore provided the basis for Korean descendants among the Yucatan Peninsula. Answer: According to the passage, there were 802 men and 231 women and children. To find the difference, we need to subtract the number of women and children from the number of men. 802 - 231 = 571. So the answer is {571}.
